te-ins\n | votes = 1,764\n | percentage = 0.08%\n | change = -0.01%\n}}\n{{Election box plurality\n | votes = 17,727\n | percentage = 0.81%\n | change = -30.49%\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n | votes = 2,184,473\n | percentage = \n | change = \n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link\n | winner = Democratic Party (United States)\n | swing =\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Personal life==\nWarner is married to Lisa Collis, whom he had met in 1984 at a [[fraternity]] party in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref name=10Things/>{{Failed verification|date=November 2017}} While on their [[honeymoon]] in 1989 in [[Egypt]] and [[Greece]], Warner became ill; when he returned home, doctors discovered he had suffered a near-fatal [[Appendicitis|burst appendix]]. Warner spent two months in the hospital recovering from the illness.<ref name=10Things/>  During her husband's tenure as governor, Collis was the first Virginia [[first lady]] to use her birth name. Warner and Collis have three daughters: Madison, Gillian, and Eliza.\n\nWarner is involved in farming and winemaking at his Rappahannock Bend farm. There, he grows {{convert|15|acre|m2}} of [[grape]]s for [[Ingleside Vineyards]]; Ingleside bottles a [[private label]] that Warner offers at [[Charitable organization|charity]] auctions.<ref name=Farming>{{cite news|last=Bedard |first=Paul |title=A Modern-Day Thomas Jefferson? |url=https://www.usnews.com/usnews/politics/whispers/articles/051128/28whisplead.htm |accessdate=March 19, 2012 |newspaper=U.S. News |date=November 20, 2005 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121215101/http://www.usnews.com/usnews/politics/whispers/articles/051128/28whisplead.htm |archivedate=January 21, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nWarner has an estimated net worth of $257 million as of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pilotonline.com/news/government/politics/nation/report-mark-warner-nd-richest-member-of-congress/article_c36f185f-1256-5b36-8d51-359cd91d9151.html|title=Report: Mark Warner 2nd richest member of Congress|first=The|last=Virginian-Pilot|publisher=|accessdate=May 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Honorary degrees==\nMark Warner has been awarded several [[honorary degrees]], these include:\n\n;Honorary degrees\n{| border=\"1\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; margin:0.5em 1em 0.5em 0; border:1px #056 solid; border-collapse:collapse;\"\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#f5f5f5; width:20%;\"| <span style=\"color:dimGrey;\">Location</span> !!  style=\"background:#f5f5f5; width:20%;\"| <span style=\"color:dimGrey;\">Date</span> !!  style=\"background:#f5f5f5; width:40%;\"| <span style=\"color:dimGrey;\">School</span> !!  style=\"background:#f5f5f5; width:20%;\"| <span style=\"color:dimGrey;\">Degree</span>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Virginia}} || '''2002''' || [[College of William and Mary]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wm.edu/news/stories/2018/dont-check-out-warner-encourages-wm-grads-to-be-active-citizens.php|title='Don\u2019t check out': Warner encourages W&M grads to be active citizens|website=www.wm.edu|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|District of Columbia}} || '''2003''' || [[George Washington University]] || Doctor of Public Service (DPS)  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://provost.gwu.edu/honorary-degree-recipients|title=Honorary Degree Recipients - Office of the Provost - The George Washington University|website=provost.gwu.edu|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|North Carolina}} || '''15 May 2006''' || [[Wake Forest University]] || [[Doctor of Laws]] (LL.D)  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://commencement.news.wfu.edu/2000s/c2006/2006-honorary-degrees/|title=2006: Honorary degrees|website=Commencement News|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Virginia}} || '''2007''' || [[Lord Fairfax Community College]] || Associate of Humane Letters\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Virginia}} || '''20 May 2007''' || [[Eastern Virginia Medical School]] || Doctorate  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://pilotonline.com/news/article_146a5736-76fc-53b2-aaf5-1368105f442e.html|title=Mark Warner tells EVMS grads their degrees are 'tickets' to success|first=The|last=Virginian-Pilot|website=Virginian-Pilot|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Virginia}} || '''25 May 2013''' || [[George Mason University]] || Doctorate  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?312854-1/george-mason-university-commencement-address|title=George Mason University Commencement Address, May 18 2013 - Video - C-SPAN.org|website=www.c-span.org|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Flagu|Virginia}} || '''19 May 2018''' || [[Virginia State University]] || Doctorate  <ref>{{cite web|url=http://richmondfreepress.com/news/2018/may/19/lt-gov-justin-e-fairfax-and-us-sen-mark-r-warner-e/|title=Lt. Gov. Justin E. Fairfax and U.S. Sen. Mark R. Warner encourage VSU graduates at dual commencement ceremonies|website=richmondfreepress.com|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n{{Expand list|date=June 2018}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of celebrities who own wineries and vineyards]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons}}\n* [https://warner.senate.gov/ Senator Mark Warner] official U.S. Senate website\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Virginia/Government/Federal/US_Senate/Mark_Warner_%5BD%5D}}\n* {{C-SPAN|markwarner02}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090717102119/http://www.forwardtogetherpac.com/ Forward Together PAC]\n;Archival records\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051231015606/http://www.governor.virginia.gov/ Archived website of the Office of the Virginia Governor]\n* [https://wayback.archive-it.org/190/*/http://www.governor.virginia.gov/ Archived website of Virginia Governor Mark R. Warner, 2005-2006] part of [http://www.archive-it.org/public/collection.html?id=190 Virginia's Political Landscape 2005 Web Archive Collection] at [http://www.virginiamemory.com/collections/archival_web_collections Virginia Memory]\n* [http://ead.lib.virginia.edu/vivaead/publi