{"title_page": "Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge e Pigeiros", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge e Pigeiros\n|image_shield = \n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|metro              = [[Metropolitan Area of Porto|Porto]]\n|district           = [[Aveiro District|Aveiro]]\n|municipality       = [[Santa Maria da Feira]]\n|area_total = 10.64\n|population_total = 3897\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates = {{coord|40.969|-8.500|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = \n|footnotes =\n}}\n'''Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge e Pigeiros''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Santa Maria da Feira]], Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merger of the former parishes [[Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge]] and [[Pigeiros]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 106-107|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=30 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 3,897,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 10.64&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906094624/http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls |date=September 6, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Santa Maria da Feira}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caldas de Sao Jorge e Pigeiros}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Santa Maria da Feira]]\n\n\n{{Aveiro-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge e Pigeiros\n|image_shield = \n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|metro              = [[Metropolitan Area of Porto|Porto]]\n|district           = [[Aveiro District|Aveiro]]\n|municipality       = [[Santa Maria da Feira]]\n|area_total = 10.64\n|population_total = 3897\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates = {{coord|40.969|-8.500|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = \n|footnotes =\n}}\n'''Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge e Pigeiros''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Santa Maria da Feira]], Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merger of the former parishes [[Caldas de S\u00e3o Jorge]] and [[Pigeiros]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 106-107|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=30 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 3,897,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 10.64&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906094624/http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls |date=September 6, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Santa Maria da Feira}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caldas de Sao Jorge e Pigeiros}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Santa Maria da Feira]]\n\n\n{{Aveiro-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caldas_de_S%C3%A3o_Jorge_e_Pigeiros"}
{"title_page": "Caldas das Taipas", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Caldas das Taipas\n|image_skyline      = Ara de Trajano 02.JPG\n|image_caption      = Ara de Trajano\n|image_flag         = Pt-gmrct1.PNG\n|image_shield       = GMR-caldastaipas.PNG\n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Guimar\u00e3es]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|41.486|-8.348|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          =\n|area_total         = 2.69\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 5723\n|patron             = [[Thomas the Apostle|Saint Thomas]]\n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = https://caldasdastaipas.com/\n}}\n'''Caldas das Taipas''' (officially: ''Caldelas'') is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Guimar\u00e3es]], Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 57-58|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=5 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 5,723,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 2.69&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Town status received 1940-06-19.\n\nDuring the [[Roman Era]] there were some testimonies, like the [[Ara de Trajano]], with inscriptions to the emperor. Several vestiges of that time were found in the place where the first bathhouse was installed, which later became what is now known as the ''Old Baths''.\n\nThe discovery of new water sources and the need to construct new facilities for the hot springs determined the location of what is now known as the ''New Baths''. After a period of interregnum, the thermal baths resumed their operation in the 1980s and have since been developing technical improvements, with the aim of extending the services. In addition to the thermal baths, there is a camping complex, a complex of swimming pools and a natural park that margins the [[Ave River]].\n\nThe town has experienced great growth both in terms of the resident population and in terms of urban agglomeration. This growth is explained by the appearance of the [[cutlery]] industry and the proximity to two important cities - [[Braga]] and [[Guimar\u00e3es]] and the improvement of access to these cities. The uncontrolled growth led to situations of rupture and the road connection to Guimar\u00e3es is made with some difficulty, due to the high traffic that is registered along that route.\n\n== Associations ==\n* Banda Musical de Caldas das Taipas (Musical Band of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Clube Ca\u00e7adores das Taipas (Hunters of Taipas Club)\n* Centro de Actividades Recreativas Taipense (Center of Recreative Activities Taipense)\n* Rotary Club de Caldas das Taipas (Rotary Club of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Centro Social Pe. Manuel Joaquim de Sousa (Social Center Pe. Manuel Joaquim de Sousa)\n* Clube de T\u00e9nis (Tennis Club)\n* Clube de T\u00e9nis de Mesa (Table Tennis Club)\n* Clube de Ca\u00e7a do Vale do Ave (Hunting Club of Ave Valley)\n* Clube de Pesca (Fishing Club)\n* CNE - Agrupamento 666 de Caldas das Taipas\n* Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Humanit\u00e1ria dos Bombeiros Volunt\u00e1rios de Caldas das Taipas (Humanitarian Association of Voluntary Firefighters of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Movimento Art\u00edstico das Taipas - Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Cultural (Artistic Movement of Taipas - Cultural Association)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Guimar\u00e3es]]\n\n\n{{Braga-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Caldas das Taipas\n|image_skyline      = Ara de Trajano 02.JPG\n|image_caption      = Ara de Trajano\n|image_flag         = Pt-gmrct1.PNG\n|image_shield       = GMR-caldastaipas.PNG\n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Guimar\u00e3es]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|41.486|-8.348|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          =\n|area_total         = 2.69\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 5723\n|patron             = [[Thomas the Apostle|Saint Thomas]]\n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = https://caldasdastaipas.com/\n}}\n'''Caldas das Taipas''' (officially: ''Caldelas'') is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Guimar\u00e3es]], Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 57-58|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=5 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 5,723,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 2.69&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Town status received 1940-06-19.\n\nDuring the [[Roman Era]] there were some testimonies, like the [[Ara de Trajano]], with inscriptions to the emperor. Several vestiges of that time were found in the place where the first bathhouse was installed, which later became what is now known as the ''Old Baths''.\n\nThe discovery of new water sources and the need to construct new facilities for the hot springs determined the location of what is now known as the ''New Baths''. After a period of interregnum, the thermal baths resumed their operation in the 1980s and have since been developing technical improvements, with the aim of extending the services. In addition to the thermal baths, there is a camping complex, a complex of swimming pools and a natural park that margins the [[Ave River]].\n\nThe town has experienced great growth both in terms of the resident population and in terms of urban agglomeration. This growth is explained by the appearance of the [[cutlery]] industry and the proximity to two important cities - [[Braga]] and [[Guimar\u00e3es]] and the improvement of access to these cities. The uncontrolled growth led to situations of rupture and the road connection to Guimar\u00e3es is made with some difficulty, due to the high traffic that is registered along that route.\n\n== Associations ==\n* Banda Musical de Caldas das Taipas (Musical Band of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Clube Ca\u00e7adores das Taipas (Hunters of Taipas Club)\n* Centro de Actividades Recreativas Taipense (Center of Recreative Activities Taipense)\n* Rotary Club de Caldas das Taipas (Rotary Club of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Centro Social Pe. Manuel Joaquim de Sousa (Social Center Pe. Manuel Joaquim de Sousa)\n* Clube de T\u00e9nis (Tennis Club)\n* Clube de T\u00e9nis de Mesa (Table Tennis Club)\n* Clube de Ca\u00e7a do Vale do Ave (Hunting Club of Ave Valley)\n* Clube de Pesca (Fishing Club)\n* CNE - Agrupamento 666 de Caldas das Taipas\n* Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Humanit\u00e1ria dos Bombeiros Volunt\u00e1rios de Caldas das Taipas (Humanitarian Association of Voluntary Firefighters of Caldas das Taipas)\n* Movimento Art\u00edstico das Taipas - Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Cultural (Artistic Movement of Taipas - Cultural Association)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Guimar\u00e3es]]\n\n\n{{Braga-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caldas_das_Taipas"}
